Question 12

You didn't Attempt

Consider the following statements:

S1 : When the cache block size decreases tag directory size increases.

S2: Fully associative cache needs more number of comparators to match tag bits compared to direct mapped cache.

Select the correct option.

S1 is true

S2 is true

both are true

Correct answer

none of them true

Solution

Hide

S1: For a given cache size, if the cache block is reduced, then the cache can accommodate more cache blocks. Since the number of cache blocks has increased we can see that the TAG directory size will increase according to the above calculation.

S2 is true because in fully associative cache, we need to compare all blocks in parallel. So we will need as many comparators as number of blocks.

Question 27

You didn't Attempt

Consider the following statements:

1. Let T be the DFS tree resulting from DFS traversal on a connected directed graph the root of the tree is an articulation point, iff it has at least two children.

2. When BFS is carried out on a directed graph G, the edges of G will be classified as tree edge, back edge, or cross edge and not forward edge as in the case of DFS.

True both

Correct answer

False both

True 1 only

True 2 only

Solution

Hide

1) An articulation point is a node which when deleted splits the graph into more than one component. This can be found out by performing DFS on the graph. The root of the DFS tree can only be an articulation point iff it has more than one child. Hence this is TRUE.

2) For case of a BFS on a directed graph there can only be tree, back or cross edges and distinguishing between cross and back edges cannot be done based on the order of traversal alone, contrary to the case of a DFS. This is also TRUE.

Question 29

You didn't Attempt

The following C function takes a single-linked list of integers as a parameter and rearranges the elements of the list. The function is called with the list containing the integers 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1 in the given order. What will be the contents of the list after function completes execution?

struct node

{

int value;

struct node *next;

};

void rearrange(struct node *list)

{

struct node *p, * q;

int temp;

if ((!list) || !list->next)

return;

p = list;

q = list->next;

while(q)

{

temp = p->value;

p->value = q->value;

q->value = temp;

p = q->next;

q = p?p->next:0;

}

}

1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8

7, 8, 5, 6, 3, 4, 1, 2

Correct answer

8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1

7, 8, 4, 5, 6, 1, 2, 3

Solution

Hide

The function rearrange() exchanges data of every node with its next node. It starts exchanging data from the first node itself.

Question 37

You didn't Attempt

Consider a 32-bit machine where four-level paging scheme is used. If the hit ratio to TLB is 98%, and it takes 20 nanosecond to search the TLB and 100 nanoseconds to access the main memory what is effective memory access time in nanoseconds?

128

Correct answer

130

125

none of the above

Solution

Hide

Hit ratio to TLB(H) is 98%

Searching time of TLB(T) is 20ns

Access time(M) is 100ns and four level paging scheme is used.

Effective Memory access Time, EAT = H* T+ (1 - H)[ T+ 4*M] + M]

EAT = (0.98 *20) + 0.02(20 + 400) + 100

= 19.6 + 8.4 + 100 = 128 ns

Question 43

You didn't Attempt

In an interleaved memory, there will be ____ banks of DRAM, while conceptually describing one bank of memory that is twice as large as second one.

-

Your answer

2

Correct answer

Solution

Hide

In interleaved memory there will be 2 banks of DRAM, while conceptually describing one bank of memory that is twice as large as second one. Interleaved memory is a technique for improvising the speed of DRAM (Dynamic Random Access Memory). In this technique, the main memory will be divided into memory banks that can be accessed individually without depending on one another. The CPU can access sections intermittently without waiting for the relevant memory to be stored.

Question 48

You didn't Attempt

We are interested in topological orderings of the following DAG which satisfy the constraint that whenever 2 appears before 3, 8 must appear before 9. How many such orderings are there___?

-

Your answer

10

Correct answer

Solution

Hide

There are 2 blocks {2} || {3,4,5} and {7,8} || {9} that can be reordered.

There are 4 ways of ordering the left block, of which only 1, 2-3-4-5 has 2 before 3.

There are 3 ways of ordering the right block, of which only 1 7-8-9, has 8 before 9.

So there is 3 * 3 = 9 unconstrained topological orders, plus one that meets the constraint.

Orderings = 9+1 = 10

Consider a cache memory which does not contain anything(empty). It is of size 64 KB and size of one block is 16 KB. The cache memory is

direct-mapped. Assume that processor requests the main memory blocks in the following order:

0, 5, 8, 33, 8, 2, 22, 33, 5, 8

The hit ratio using FIFO replacement policy is (upto one decimal place) _____________.

(Answer up to one decimal place)

-

Your answer

0.3

Correct answer

Solution

Hide

Number of lines = 64KB/16KB =4

The formula used to map main memory block is k mod n, where k is the main memory block number, n is the number of lines in cache. All the main memory blocks will be mapped using the formula and replaced using FIFO as described below:

#misses = 7

#hits = 3

Hit ratio = 3/10=0.3
